cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper proposes a model for incremental class learning using a brain-inspired dual-memory system, which involves consolidating new memories from a network for recent memories inspired by the mammalian hippocampal complex to a network for long-term storage inspired by medial prefrontal cortex. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
